nested_items.name: inlineRedactionConfiguration
nested_items.description: The inline redaction configuration for the data protection settings.

nested_items.name: globalConfidenceLevel
nested_items.description: The global confidence level for the inline redaction configuration. This indicates the certainty of data type matches in the redaction process. Confidence level 3 means high confidence, and requires a formatted text pattern match in order for content to be redacted. Confidence level 2 means medium confidence, and redaction considers both formatted and unformatted text, and adds keyword associate to the logic. Confidence level 1 means low confidence, and redaction is enforced for both formatted pattern + unformatted pattern without keyword. This is applied to patterns that do not have a pattern-level confidence level. Defaults to confidence level 2.

nested_items.name: globalEnforcedUrls
nested_items.description: The global enforced URL configuration for the inline redaction configuration. This is applied to patterns that do not have a pattern-level enforced URL list.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: globalExemptUrls
nested_items.description: The global exempt URL configuration for the inline redaction configuration. This is applied to patterns that do not have a pattern-level exempt URL list.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: inlineRedactionPatterns
nested_items.description: The inline redaction patterns to be enabled for the inline redaction configuration.

nested_items.name: builtInPatternId
nested_items.description: The built-in pattern from the list of preconfigured patterns. Either a customPattern or builtInPatternId is required.

nested_items.name: confidenceLevel
nested_items.description: The confidence level for inline redaction pattern. This indicates the certainty of data type matches in the redaction process. Confidence level 3 means high confidence, and requires a formatted text pattern match in order for content to be redacted. Confidence level 2 means medium confidence, and redaction considers both formatted and unformatted text, and adds keyword associate to the logic. Confidence level 1 means low confidence, and redaction is enforced for both formatted pattern + unformatted pattern without keyword. This overrides the global confidence level.

nested_items.name: customPattern
nested_items.description: >The configuration for a custom pattern. Either a customPattern or builtInPatternId is required.

nested_items.name: keywordRegex
nested_items.description: The keyword regex for the customer pattern. After there is a match to the pattern regex, the keyword regex is used to search within the proximity of the match. If there is a keyword match, then the match is confirmed. If no keyword regex is provided, the pattern regex match will automatically be confirmed. The format must follow JavaScript regex format. The pattern must be enclosed between slashes, and can have flags behind the second slash. For example, '/ab+c/gi'

nested_items.name: patternDescription
nested_items.description: The pattern description for the customer pattern.

nested_items.name: patternName
nested_items.description: The pattern name for the custom pattern.

nested_items.name: patternRegex
nested_items.description: The pattern regex for the customer pattern. The format must follow JavaScript regex format. The pattern must be enclosed between slashes, and can have flags behind the second slash. For example: '/ab+c/gi'.

nested_items.name: enforcedUrls
nested_items.description: The enforced URL configuration for the inline redaction pattern. This will override the global enforced URL configuration.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: exemptUrls
nested_items.description: The exempt URL configuration for the inline redaction pattern. This will override the global exempt URL configuration for the inline redaction pattern.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: redactionPlaceHolder
nested_items.description: The redaction placeholder that will replace the redacted text in session for the inline redaction pattern.

nested_items.name: redactionPlaceHolderText
nested_items.description: The redaction placeholder text that will replace the redacted text in session for the custom text redaction placeholder type.

nested_items.name: redactionPlaceHolderType
nested_items.description: The redaction placeholder type that will replace the redacted text in session.
